value.Title: Technology, Strategy, & War
value.Description: Cross list with CIT 48101. Will be offered online., The purpose of this course is to teach students to think strategically. But it will not stop there. The course is also designed to thrust students into the role of actual decision-makers and allow them to experience making difficult choices of their own. Students will be challenged to think critically, first to understand the foundational principles of strategic thought and then to apply their own approaches to modern national security problems. The goal of this course is to help students learn how to make assessments, develop options, and make decisions about military investments,  operations, and strategies to achieve overall national objectives. Students will learn how the choices about technology and strategy accumulate to propel the course of events towards peace or war.
